<TITLE> BFF seeks appointment with AFC chief </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 30 (bdnews24.com)  The Bangladesh Football Federation (BFF) has sought an appointment with Asian Football Confederation (AFC) president Mohamed Bin Hammam to discuss football associations (FAs) at district and divisional levels. "We have sought an appointment with Hammam to discuss the FAs," BFF acting president Monir Ahmed told bdnews24.com Wednesday. "A four-strong delegation may meet Hammam if the AFC president gives us some time, " he added. The decision to seek appointment came at a BFF emergency meeting Tuesday. A few days back, a meeting of the Bangladesh Olympic Association (BOA), BFF and some renowned organisers decided to send a five-strong delegation to see the AFC president about the importance of installing government officials in FAs. The move came as the global football regulator FIFA was against inclusion of a government official in any Divisional and District Football Associations (FAs) in Bangladesh. But local football organisers and officials want government officials to play their role in the associations. In April last year, FIFA asked the BFF to form FAs at district and divisional levels keeping the government officials out of the committees. But there is a growing concern whether it will be possible to organise football competitions in the divisional and district levels without the help of local government officials. b
